#. <section class="sutta" id="sn16.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn16.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 16"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 16"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Kassapavagga"
msgstr "1. Kassapa"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 4. Kulūpakasutta → kulūpagasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn16.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Kulūpakasutta"
msgstr "4. Visiting Families"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn16.4:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn16.4:1.2"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "“What do you think, mendicants? "

#. VAR: kulūpako → kulūpago (bj)
msgctxt "sn16.4:1.3"
msgid ""
"kathaṃrūpo bhikkhu arahati kulūpako hotuṃ, kathaṃrūpo bhikkhu na arahati "
"kulūpako hotun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What kind of mendicant is worthy of visiting families? And what kind of "
"mendicant is not worthy of visiting families?”"

msgctxt "sn16.4:1.4"
msgid "Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …"
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”"

msgctxt "sn16.4:1.5"
msgid "bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.201"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn16.4:2.1"
msgid "“Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃcitto kulāni upasaṅkamati:"
msgstr "“Whoever visits families with the thought:"

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.2"
msgid "‘dentuyeva me, mā nādaṃsu;"
msgstr "‘May they give to me, may they not fail to give."

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.3"
msgid "bahukaññeva me dentu, mā thokaṃ;"
msgstr "May they give a lot, not a little."

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.4"
msgid "paṇītaññeva me dentu, mā lūkhaṃ;"
msgstr "May they give me fine things, not coarse."

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.5"
msgid "sīghaññeva me dentu, mā dandhaṃ;"
msgstr "May they give quickly, not slowly."

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.6"
msgid "sakkaccaññeva me dentu, mā asakkaccan’ti."
msgstr "May they give carefully, not carelessly.’"

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.7"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno evaṃcittassa kulāni upasaṅkamato na denti, "
"tena bhikkhu sandīyati; so tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant with such a thought approaches a family and they don’t give, "
"the mendicant feels slighted. And they experience pain and sadness because "
"of that."

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.8"
msgid "Thokaṃ denti, no bahukaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "If they give only a little …"

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.9"
msgid "lūkhaṃ denti, no paṇītaṃ …"
msgstr "if they give coarse things …"

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.10"
msgid ""
"dandhaṃ denti, no sīghaṃ, tena bhikkhu sandīyati; so tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ "
"domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr "if they give slowly …"

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.11"
msgid ""
"Asakkaccaṃ denti, no sakkaccaṃ; tena bhikkhu sandīyati; so tatonidānaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr ""
"if they give carelessly, the mendicant feels slighted. And they experience "
"pain and sadness because of that."

msgctxt "sn16.4:2.12"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na arahati kulūpako hotuṃ."
msgstr "That kind of mendicant is not worthy of visiting families."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn16.4:3.1"
msgid "Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃcitto kulāni upasaṅkamati:"
msgstr "Whoever visits families with the thought:"

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.2"
msgid "‘taṃ kutettha labbhā parakulesu—"
msgstr "‘When among other families, how could I possibly think:"

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.3"
msgid "dentuyeva me, mā nādaṃsu;"
msgstr "“May they give to me, may they not fail to give."

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.4"
msgid "bahukaññeva me dentu, mā thokaṃ;"
msgstr "May they give a lot, not a little."

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.5"
msgid "paṇītaññeva me dentu, mā lūkhaṃ;"
msgstr "May they give me fine things, not coarse."

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.6"
msgid "sīghaññeva me dentu, mā dandhaṃ;"
msgstr "May they give quickly, not slowly."

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.7"
msgid "sakkaccaññeva me dentu, mā asakkaccan’ti."
msgstr "May they give carefully, not carelessly.”’"

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.8"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno evaṃcittassa kulāni upasaṅkamato na denti; "
"tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant with such a thought approaches a family and they don’t give, "
"the mendicant doesn’t feel slighted. And they don’t experience pain and "
"sadness because of that."

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.9"
msgid ""
"Thokaṃ denti, no bahukaṃ; tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr "If they give only a little …"

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.10"
msgid ""
"Lūkhaṃ denti, no paṇītaṃ; tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr "if they give coarse things …"

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.11"
msgid ""
"Dandhaṃ denti, no sīghaṃ; tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr "if they give slowly …"

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.12"
msgid ""
"Asakkaccaṃ denti, no sakkaccaṃ; tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr ""
"if they give carelessly, the mendicant doesn’t feel slighted. And they don’t "
"experience pain and sadness because of that."

msgctxt "sn16.4:3.13"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahati kulūpako hotuṃ."
msgstr "That kind of mendicant is worthy of visiting families."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.202"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn16.4:4.1"
msgid "Kassapo, bhikkhave, evaṃcitto kulāni upasaṅkamati:"
msgstr "Kassapa visits families with the thought:"

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.2"
msgid "‘taṃ kutettha labbhā parakulesu—"
msgstr "‘When among other families, how could I possibly think:"

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.3"
msgid "dentuyeva me, mā nādaṃsu;"
msgstr "“May they give to me, may they not fail to give."

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.4"
msgid "bahukaññeva me dentu, mā thokaṃ;"
msgstr "May they give a lot, not a little."

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.5"
msgid "paṇītaññeva me dentu, mā lūkhaṃ;"
msgstr "May they give me fine things, not coarse."

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.6"
msgid "sīghaññeva me dentu, mā dandhaṃ;"
msgstr "May they give quickly, not slowly."

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.7"
msgid "sakkaccaññeva me dentu, mā asakkaccan’ti."
msgstr "May they give carefully, not carelessly.”’"

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.8"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, bhikkhave, kassapassa evaṃcittassa kulāni upasaṅkamato na denti; "
"tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr ""
"With such a thought, if he approaches a family and they don’t give, he doesn’"
"t feel slighted. And he doesn’t experience pain and sadness because of that."

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.9"
msgid ""
"Thokaṃ denti, no bahukaṃ; tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr "If they give only a little …"

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.10"
msgid ""
"Lūkhaṃ denti, no paṇītaṃ; tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr "if they give coarse things …"

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.11"
msgid ""
"Dandhaṃ denti, no sīghaṃ; tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr "if they give slowly …"

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.12"
msgid ""
"Asakkaccaṃ denti, no sakkaccaṃ; tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr ""
"if they give carelessly, he doesn’t feel slighted. And he doesn’t experience "
"pain and sadness because of that."

msgctxt "sn16.4:4.13"
msgid ""
"Kassapena vā hi vo, bhikkhave, ovadissāmi yo vā panassa kassapasadiso. "
"Ovaditehi ca pana vo tathattāya paṭipajjitabban”ti."
msgstr ""
"I will exhort you with the example of Kassapa or someone like him. You "
"should practice accordingly.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn16.4:4.14"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
